# Email Sending

Vercel serverless functions block outbound SMTP (ports 25, 465, 587). Never use Nodemailer or any SMTP transport.

## Always use Resend

```ts
import { Resend } from 'resend';
const resend = new Resend(process.env.RESEND_API_KEY);
await resend.emails.send({ from, to, replyTo, subject, html });
```

- API key env var: `RESEND_API_KEY`
- Until domain `alamiric.org` is verified in Resend, use `from: 'Al-Amir Islamic Center <onboarding@resend.dev>'`
- After domain verification, switch to `from: 'info@alamiric.org'`
- Delivery address is always `to: ['info@alamiric.org']`
